cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

The paper presents a deep learning architecture for optimal triaging of Head CTs to detect Intracranial hemorrhage (ICH). This involves segmentation and classification tasks, which are dependent on each other. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, which deals with image analysis and processing. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning, which falls under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also involves information retrieval, as it aims to decrease the time from CT acquisition to accurate ICH detection, which falls under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
